Basic Installation
==================

Follow the below Steps : 

  1) untar the binary package of shallow-parser-ben-3.0.tgz
	
        tar -xvzf shallow-parser-ben-3.0.tgz

  2) `cd' to the directory containing the package binary.

	cd shallow-parser-ben-3.0

  3.1) Export the Variable `SHALLOW_PARSER_BEN'.
 
       echo "export SHALLOW_PARSER_BEN=~/sampark/shallow_parser_ben" >> ~/.bashrc

  3.2) Set the PATH to the SHALLOW_PARSER_BEN/bin/sl/sys/ben

       echo "export PATH=\$PATH:\$SHALLOW_PARSER_BEN/bin/sys/ben/" >> ~/.bashrc

  3.3) Compile the ~/.bashrc
  
       source ~/.bashrc

  4)   To Install 
       Type `make install' to install the programs, data files and
       documentation.
                   
	make install

 For how to use shallow parser for bendi, please refer to the file README-user.

 To Uninstall 
 -- ---------

     If you want to remove the program binaries and object files from the
     binary package directory type `make uninstall'. 

      make uninstall 
